🌟 Local Community Event Portal 🌟
A beginner-friendly, all-in-one HTML5 web project crafted to promote and manage local community events — no frameworks, no setup headaches. Just open and go! 🎉

📣 Overview
Local Community Event Portal is a lightweight, self-contained HTML5 project showcasing the fundamentals of modern web development. It’s the perfect hands-on guide for students, beginners, or anyone wanting to explore HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript through a practical and fun project.

🚀 Features
✨ Responsive Navigation Bar
✨ Event Registration Form
✨ Feedback Collection Section
✨ Embedded Multimedia (Images & Videos)
✨ Geolocation API Integration
✨ Local Storage for User Preferences
✨ Error Handling & Debugging Best Practices
✨ Help & FAQ Section

🖥️ How to Use
1️⃣ Clone or Download this repository:
https://github.com/panakala-praneetha
2️⃣ Open index.html in your favorite web browser — no additional setup needed!

3️⃣ Explore the Help & FAQ section via help.html for usage tips and troubleshooting.

🛠️ Tech Stack
HTML5

CSS3 (Embedded)

JavaScript (Inline)

Web APIs: Geolocation, LocalStorage

Multimedia: Images, Video

🎓 Learning Goals
✅ Master embedding CSS & JS directly within HTML
✅ Build accessible, responsive web forms
✅ Integrate browser-native Web APIs
✅ Manage user preferences using LocalStorage
✅ Practice real-time debugging in browsers

